The police on Monday arraigned Mr. Kehinde Odunlade, 27, at an Ile-Ife Magistratesâ€™ Court in Osun State for allegedly defiling a 15-year-old girl. The defendant was arraigned on a two-count charge of conspiracy and indecent assault. Prosecuting Inspector Sunday Osanyintuyi alleged that the defendant committed the offence last December 22 around 10am, at Igboya, Ile-Ife. He said the offence contravened sections 360 and 516 of the Criminal Code, Laws of Osun, 2002. The defendant pleaded not guilty. Defence counsel Mr. Olurotimi Oyebuade urged the court to grant his client bail in most liberal terms. He said his client would not jump bail, adding that he would produce reliable sureties. Magistrate Muhibah Olatunji granted Odunlade bail in the sum of N500,000, with two sureties in the like sum. She said that the sureties, who must live within the court jurisdiction, must be civil servants not below Grade Level 10 and must swear to affidavit of means. Olatunji added that the sureties must produce three-year tax clearance certificates and that their houses must be verified by the prosecutor. She adjourned the case till February 10.